@database CMClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - CM Class"


CM class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "GroupClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The CM class is used to create a CManager object.

  CM is a subclass of CManager.mcc so you must have CManager.mcc
  in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. CManager and CManager.mcc are
  copyright of Simone Tellini.

  A CManager object is a group like that one that appears in the
  CManager main window.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AutoLoad@{fg text}
  B I
  If 1, the object will load its data the first time it is drawn;
  If 0, the data must be load via LoadData method

  @{fg shine}Changed@{fg text}
  B SGN

  @{fg shine}DoubleClick@{fg text}
  S IGN G2N

  @{fg shine}HideChat@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}HideFtp@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}HideTelnet@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}HideUsers@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}HideWWW@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}NoMenu@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}Path@{fg text}
  S G

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}


 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}LoadData@{fg text}

  @{fg shine}SaveData@{fg text}

  @{fg shine}Search@{fg text}

  @{fg shine}Sort@{fg text}

@EndNode

